{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"3f859c65-1d82-4e85-883d-842dd810db7f","content":"The tutorial is **partially right but partially outdated/incorrect** for .NET MAUI on .NET 10:\n\n### ✅ `ios:Page.UseSafeArea=\"True\"` — Correct\nThis works in .NET MAUI. Make sure you use the **MAUI namespace**, not the old Xamarin.Forms one:\n\n```xml\nxmlns:ios=\"clr-namespace:Microsoft.Maui.Controls.PlatformConfiguration.iOSSpecific;assembly=Microsoft.Maui.Controls\"\n```\n\nThen on your `ContentPage`:\n```xml\nios:Page.UseSafeArea=\"True\"\n```\n\nThis automatically insets page content to avoid the notch/Dynamic Island and home indicator.\n\n### ❌ `IgnoreSafeArea=\"True\"` — Not a real MAUI API\nThere is **no built-in `IgnoreSafeArea` property** on `Grid` or any layout in .NET MAUI. That tutorial is likely wrong or referring to a custom implementation.\n\n### Background image behind the safe area\nTo let a background bleed edge-to-edge while keeping content safe, **don't use `UseSafeArea`** on the page. Instead, manually pad your content:\n\n```xml\n<ContentPage xmlns:ios=\"clr-namespace:Microsoft.Maui.Controls.PlatformConfiguration.iOSSpecific;assembly=Microsoft.Maui.Controls\">\n    <Grid>\n        <!-- Full-bleed background -->\n        <Image Source=\"bg.png\" Aspect=\"AspectFill\" />\n\n        <!-- Content respects safe area via padding -->\n        <StackLayout Padding=\"{OnPlatform iOS='20,64,20,34'}\">\n            <Label Text=\"Hello, safe area!\" />\n        </StackLayout>\n    </Grid>\n</ContentPage>\n```\n\nOr set the safe area padding programmatically using `On<iOS>().SetSafeAreaInsets()` for dynamic values. This gives you full control over which elements respect the safe area and which don't.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"36aa6f79-d0e2-4c86-b024-b279ecd5facd","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The repository doesn't have relevant MAUI content. Let me answer based on my knowledge of .NET MAUI safe area APIs.\n\nIn .NET MAUI, the safe area handling has evolved:\n\n1. `ios:Page.UseSafeArea=\"True\"` — This is the **legacy Xamarin.Forms** platform-specific API (`Xamarin.Forms.PlatformConfiguration.iOSSpecific`). In .NET MAUI, this was carried forward initially but the recommended approach changed.\n\n2. In .NET MAUI (starting around .NET 8/9), the recommended way to handle safe areas is different. \n\nThe `Page.UseSafeArea` property still exists but migrated from the Xamarin.Forms namespace to the Microsoft.Maui.Controls namespace, so you'd reference it with the updated iOS platform-specific XML namespace pointing to the MAUI assembly instead.\n\n`IgnoreSafeArea` isn't a built-in MAUI property on Grid or other layouts—it doesn't exist in the framework, so if someone's trying to use it, they'd need a different approach to handle safe area behavior. use `UseSafeArea` at the page level. Instead, I'd manually pad the content or use a hybrid approach where the background extends behind the safe area but the actual content stays inset. So `UseSafeArea` with the proper MAUI namespace is the right call, but `IgnoreSafeArea` isn't a real MAUI property — that tutorial is likely mixing frameworks or describing a custom workaround.","outputTokens":1287,"requestId":"D444:7818E:1CED881:207A080:6A07C0A2"},"id":"d90554e3-13dd-4f2b-b2ec-41774b60e608","timestamp":"2026-05-16T00:56:24.889Z","parentId":"7c040c26-11f9-4b4f-9411-4429290d087a"}
